<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15946">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Snow%20Sports.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15947">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15947 mb-requirement-id-15948">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the hazards you are most likely to
        encounter while participating in snow sport activities, and what you
        should do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these
        hazards. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/AKxY8Xm-Gg0?si=EK3y5wxrfgJTmAk9"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Ski Safely (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://centerforspineandortho.com/common-skiing-and-snowboarding-injuries-and-how-to-prevent-them/%20"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Prevent Injuries (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15947 mb-requirement-id-15949">
        (b) Discuss first aid and prevention for the types of injuries or
        illnesses that could occur while participating in snow sports, including
        hypothermia, frostbite, shock, dehydration, sunburn, concussion,
        fractures, bruises, sprains, and strains. Tell how to apply splints.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/tHiav9zYJT0?si=VC-plNy5tA2XSZ1I"
          target="_blank"
          >Treating Frostbite and Hypothermia (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/jo2zi_JB9_4?si=nVI-3TY16Ma1BL1p"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Splint a Broken Bone (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15950">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15950 mb-requirement-id-15951">
        (a) Explain why every snow sport participant should be prepared to
        render first aid in the event of an accident.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15950 mb-requirement-id-15952">
        (b) Explain the procedure used to report an accident to the local ski
        patrol or local emergency personnel. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Zl0ZyNoox8M?si=xgYuHNUn5izc4HA7"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Report an Accident to the Ski Patrol (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16005">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Explain the international trail-marking system. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/N_f6xMFVVHc" target="_blank"
        >International Trail Marking System (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16006">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Discuss the importance of strength, endurance, and flexibility in snow
      sports. Demonstrate exercises and activities you can do to get fit for the
      option you choose in requirement 7. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/a8sf5k3fH9I" target="_blank"
        >Training to Prevent Snow Sports Injuries (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16007">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Present yourself properly clothed and equipped for the option you choose
      in requirement 7. Discuss how the clothing you have chosen will help keep
      you warm and protected. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/mjJNpR3nepM" target="_blank"
        >How to Dress for Snow Sports (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15953">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do ALL of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15953 mb-requirement-id-15954">
        (a) Explain the elements of the <i>Your Responsibility Code</i> that is
        in effect at the location whehre you will ski, snowboard, or snowshoe.
        Explain why each person must follow this code. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/euGO92z4MnM" target="_blank"
          >Your Responsibility Code (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15953 mb-requirement-id-15955">
        (b) Explain the <i>SMART Style</i> safety program. Tell why it is
        important and how it applies to participants at snow sport venues like
        terrain parks and pipes. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4Y7lCN7SKiY" target="_blank"
          ><i>SMART</i> Style Safety Program (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15953 mb-requirement-id-15956">
        (c) Explain the precautions pertaining to avalanche safety, including
        the responsibility of individuals regarding avalanche safety. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_f-vEc5LTFM" target="_blank"
          >How to Reduce Avalanche Risk (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15957">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do ONE of the following options:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15957 mb-requirement-id-15958">
        <strong>Option A—Downhill (Alpine) Skiing. </strong>Do ALL of the
        following: <br /><br /><b>Note:</b> Generally, a gentle slope will be a
        trail designated by a green circle, a slightly steeper slope will be a
        green circle or blue square trail, and an intermediate slope will be a
        blue square trail. However, your counselor should determine what type of
        hill is most suited to your skill level and allows you to demonstrate
        each of the required skills.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15959">
        (1) Show how to wax and maintain your skis and use/maintain your release
        bindings. Explain the international DIN standard and what it means to
        skiers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1Xt1gZfZ2Rw" target="_blank"
          >How to Wax Skis (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ix27SNEsRYM" target="_blank"
          >How to Test Ski Bindings (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DkNAXgc2-rk?si=p-0U6YH1kIngZ47t"
          target="_blank"
          >Ski Binding DIN Settings (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15960">
        (2) Explain the American Teaching System and a basic snowskiing
        progression. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Snow%20Sports/american_teaching_system_levels.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >American Teaching System Skill Levels (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15961">
        (3) Discuss the different types of Alpine skis. Demonstrate two ways to
        carry skis and poles safely and easily. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PXR5vRgIlJE" target="_blank"
          >Types of Alpine Skis (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GLu49jDy51k" target="_blank"
          >How to Carry Skis (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15962">
        (4) Demonstrate how to ride one kind of lift and explain how to ride two
        others. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4xkGmEC-vPk" target="_blank"
          >Ski Lifts and How to Ride Them (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15963">
        (5) On a gentle slope, demonstrate some of the beginning maneuvers
        learned in skiing. Include the straight run, gliding wedge, wedge stop,
        sidestep, and herringbone maneuvers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/LaF1tT1l7c0?si=A4krxuBaIP1wPGgx"
          target="_blank"
          >Beginner's Guide - The Gear (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/l6AG5WLUaNo?si=Cy7fDWXKwAFsQp9B"
          target="_blank"
          >Beginner's Guide - Basic Moves (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zAQVuC1Q4mw?si=ofT18Us8eaEUr9_w"
          target="_blank"
          >Beginner's Guide - Getting Around (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15964">
        (6) On slightly steeper terrain, show linked wedge turns. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1BdMf9rmubQ" target="_blank"
          >How to Do Linked Wedge Turns (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/9bEH6JCq83U?si=5ru69RVAgDgQfAif"
          target="_blank"
          >The Wedge Turn (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15965">
        (7) On a moderate slope, demonstrate five to 10 christies. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/x5q0yV14sas" target="_blank"
          >How to Do Christies (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15966">
        (8) Make a controlled run down an intermediate slope. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CMgId4iSlcE" target="_blank"
          >Making a Controlled Run (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15967">
        (9) Demonstrate the ability to ski in varied conditions, including
        changes in pitch and snow conditions. Maintain your balance and ability
        to turn. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DQv53VSxykY?si=wBlVELSoFcvQ973i"
          target="_blank"
          >Skiing in Variable Snow Conditions (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15958 mb-requirement-id-15968">
        (10) Name the major ski organizations in the United States and explain
        their functions. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Z_Jh5pfseU8" target="_blank"
          >Professional Ski Instructors of America (PSIA) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MHJlZBwiUx4" target="_blank"
          >U.S. Ski &amp; Snowboard (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/bmqLYSj4u0Q?si=6X5-kAiIuDy3Tgdg"
          target="_blank"
          >National Ski Patrol (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15957 mb-requirement-id-15969">
        <strong>Option B—Cross-Country (Nordic) Skiing. </strong>DO ALL of the
        following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15970">
        (1) Show your ability to select, use, and maintain equipment for
        cross-country skiing in safety and comfort. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vqKaNOw6Feg?si=wVLxSaHGNEfQXGAq"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Choose Cross-Country Skis (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15971">
        (2) Explain the reasons for common rules, including no walking on ski
        trails, one-way ski direction, no pets, and no skiing on snowmobile
        trails.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15972">
        (3) Discuss classic, skating, touring, and telemark skis. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oXIp-lJJH4E?si=yNMZNIMyDHQjO_uC"
          target="_blank"
          >Types of Cross Country Skis (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15973">
        (4) Discuss the basic principles of waxing for cross-country ski
        touring. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/hFl9r0JapvI" target="_blank"
          >How to Wax Cross-Country Skis (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15974">
        (5) Discuss the differences between cross-country, backcountry/ski
        touring, ski mountaineering, and downhill/telemark skiing. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/a2C77sfBMHo" target="_blank"
          >Styles of Cross-Country Skiing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-B1UnHDByoY" target="_blank"
          >What is Telemark Skiing? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15975">
        (6) List the items you would take on a one-day ski tour. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3rHuEqZgUMc" target="_blank"
          >Gear Checklist for a Day Tour (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15976">
        (7) Demonstrate the proper use of a topographic map and compass.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CoVcRxza8nI" target="_blank"
          >How to Read a Topographic Map (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0cF0ovA3FtY?si=HJAgHgcZCmPOcuC3"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use a Compass (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/P1LL2FXK6o0?si=rb4_VuRCb-uql1gU"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use a Topographic Map and Compass (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15977">
        (8) On a gentle, packed slope, show some basic ways to control speed and
        direction. Include the straight run, traverse, side slip, step turn,
        wedge stop, and wedge turn maneuvers. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kmw9LxutG_8" target="_blank"
          >How to Control Speed and Direction (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15978">
        (9) On a cross-country trail, demonstrate effective propulsion by
        showing proper weight transfer form ski to ski, pole timing, rhythm,
        flow, and glide. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ctrIUq9kCJI?si=QoPaYBG0365ZvZF1"
          target="_blank"
          >Basic Moves on Cross-Country Skis (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-15979">
        (10) Demonstrate your ability, on a 4-mile tour, to cope with an average
        variety of snow conditions. <br /><b>Note:</b> Adaptive skiers may
        complete a 1-mile tour with prior approval from their counselor.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/nCqNLC8PzNM?si=_vD2U1nIhE-khHVQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Skiing on Varied Conditions (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15969 mb-requirement-id-16008">
        (11) Demonstrate several methods of dealing with steep hills or
        difficult conditions. Include traverses and kick turns going uphill and
        downhill, sidesteps, and pole drag. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/MWskz4ZnPl4?si=pyET65PzEaPCW94o"
          target="_blank"
          >Dealing With Hills (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15957 mb-requirement-id-15980">
        <strong>Option C—Snowboarding.</strong> Do ALL of the following:
        <br /><br /><b>Note:</b> Generally, a gentle slope will be a trail
        designated by a green circle, a slightly steeper slope will be a green
        circle or blue square trail, and an intermediate slope will be a blue
        square trail. However, your counselor should determine what type of hill
        is most suited to your skill level and allows you to demonstrate the
        required skills.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15984">
        (1) Discuss forward-fall injuries. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pAuRz-QP5tM" target="_blank"
          >How to Fall on a Snowboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15985">
        (2) Show your ability to select the correct equipment for snowboarding
        and to use it for safety and comfort. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/lF2lf5RGCOw?si=IonNRzzALWYLVIlx"
          target="_blank"
          >Selecting Snowboard Equipment (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15986">
        (3) Show how to use and maintain your own bindings, and explain the use
        of the different binding methods. Explain the need for leashes. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1NQ-G0qn4UA" target="_blank"
          >How to Adjust Bindings (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15987">
        (4) Discuss the four types of snowboards. Demonstrate how to carry a
        snowboard easily and safely. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/I9t_ez_utno" target="_blank"
          >Types of Snowboards (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15988">
        (5) Demonstrate how to ride one kind of lift and explain how to ride two
        others. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4xkGmEC-vPk" target="_blank"
          >Ski Lifts and How to Ride Them (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15989">
        (6) Demonstrate the basic principles of waxing a snowboard. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YGG5_xjeB2Y" target="_blank"
          >How to Wax a Snowboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15981">
        (7) Do the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15981 mb-requirement-id-15982">
        (a) On a gentle slope, demonstrate beginning snowboarding maneuvers.
        Show basic ways to control speed and direction. Include the sideslipping
        maneuver. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9YGruvaETK4" target="_blank"
          >Beginning Snowboard Maneuvers (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UoPxRNsLrZ8" target="_blank"
          >How to Make Your Board Go Straight (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15981 mb-requirement-id-15983">
        (b) On slightly steeper terrain, show traversing. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/eIcLMojBopA" target="_blank"
          >Maneuvering Hills &amp; Traversing the Slope (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15990">
        (8) On a moderate slope, demonstrate an ollie, a nose-end grab, and a
        wheelie. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/N4hCpTt30GE" target="_blank"
          >How to Do an Ollie (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gZFWW4Vus-Q" target="_blank"
          >How to Do a Nose-End Grab (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZDUHDwxqNuE" target="_blank"
          >How to Do a Wheelie (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15991">
        (9) Make a controlled run down an intermediate slope. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/77rXSf7-CWY" target="_blank"
          >Making a Controlled Run (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15992">
        (10) Demonstrate your ability to ride in varied conditions, including
        changes in pitch, snow conditions, and moguls. Maintain your balance and
        ability to turn. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/96SaQtglKHE" target="_blank"
          >Types of Snow Conditions (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15980 mb-requirement-id-15993">
        (11) Name the major snowboarding organizations in the United States and
        explain their functions. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UrtwvLd2sbU" target="_blank"
          >American Association of Snowboarding Instructors (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15957 mb-requirement-id-15994">
        <strong>Option D—Snowshoeing.</strong> Do ALL of the following: <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vsco4SkXSTc?si=hyEIP4kbTHuAYHjt"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Choose Snowshoes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15994 mb-requirement-id-15995">
        (1) Name the parts of a snowshoe.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15994 mb-requirement-id-15996">
        (2) Explain how to choose the correct size of snowshoe.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15994 mb-requirement-id-15997">
        (3) Describe the different types of snowshoes and their specialized
        uses. Discuss factors to consider when choosing a snowshoe.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15994 mb-requirement-id-15998">
